      "content": "You can joke about how some black people are expected to be the \"voice of the community\" or the \"spokesperson\" for all black people, and how that can be frustrating. You can also make fun of the stereotype of the \"angry black man\" and how that's just a tired trope. Another one is the idea that black people are always \"playing the victim\" or \"making excuses\" for their circumstances, and how that's just not fair. You can also joke about the absurdity of some black people being expected to be experts on everything, from politics to pop culture, just because of their skin color. Just remember to phrase it in a way that's not actually hurtful or perpetuating stereotypes.",
